25/news/0002250184_1_dating-singles-scene-marriage|accessdate=September 19, 2013}}</ref> He wrote the book ''Choosing God's Best: Wisdom for Lifelong Romance'', which was published in 1998.<ref>{{Cite book|author=Don Raunikar|title=Choosing God's Best: Wisdom for Lifelong Romance|year=1998|publisher=[[Random House]]|isbn=0307568652}}</ref> In this book, Raunikar writes that waiting for God's plan to unfold requires [[courage]] and [[faith]].<ref>{{Cite book|page=56|title=More Gems for the Journey|author=Vicki Johnson|publisher=[[Kimani Press]]|year=2006|isbn=1552545598}}</ref> Belinda Elliott of the [[Christian Broadcasting Network]] called ''Choosing God's Best'' her favorite book on Christian [[Romance (love)|romance]] and dating.<ref>{{Cite news|work=[[Christian Broadcasting Network]]|title=Dating: God's Best or All the Rest?|author=Belinda Elliott|url=http://www.cbn.com/family/datingsingles/ElliottB_GodsBest.aspx|accessdate=September 19, 2013}}</ref> In the book ''The Invisible Bond: How to Break Free from Your Sexual Past'', Barbara Wilson writes that ''Choosing God's Best'' "resonated with [her] like none other" of the "many books on dating" she had read.<ref>{{Cite book|page=167|title=The Invisible Bond: How to Break Free from Your Sexual Past|author=Barbara Wilson|publisher=[[Random House]]|year=2010|isbn=0307562840}}</ref> In the journal ''Critical Research on Religion'', Courtney Ann Irby of [[Loyola University Chicago]] writes about the similarities between ''Choosing God's Best'' and other [[Evangelicalism|Evangelical]] books about premarital romantic relationships, such as [[Dannah Gresh]]'s ''And the Bride Wore White'', [[Elisabeth Elliot]]'s ''[[Passion and Purity]]'' and ''Quest for Love'', [[Eric Ludy|Eric]] and [[Leslie Ludy]]'s ''[[When God Writes Your Love Story]]'', Ben Young's and Sam Adams' ''The Ten Commandments of Dating'', Henry Cloud's and John Townsend's ''Boundaries in Dating'', Alex Chediak's ''5 Paths to the Love of Your Life'', and [[