The '''ITT International Fellowship Program''' was a program of [[Grant (money)|grants]] promoting international educational student exchanges, similar to the [[Fulbright Program]], sponsored by the [[ITT Corporation|International Telephone & Telegraph Corporation]]. The program was administered by the [[Institute of International Education]] from 1973 until the mid-1980s.
== History == Between 1973 and 1982, 498 students received ITT fellowships: 244 American students who went abroad for a year of study, and 254 non-US students who came to the US, usually to pursue a master's degree. Graduate students were also awarded this fellowship from 1983-1986. During this time, the fellowship was administered in conjunction with the Fulbright Program. It was considered especially prestigious at the time, because it provided students with more funding than the Fulbright Program.
===Notable alumni=== * [[Madeleine Mitchell]], violinist * [[David France]] * Susan Tintori, (to Italy, 1982, Istituto per l'Arte e Restauro), Executive Director of [[Florence Academy of Art]], Florence, Italy{{citation needed|date=August 2016}}
