{{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Laura Linnea Jensen | birth_name = | birth_date = November 16, 1948 | birth_place = Tacoma, Washington | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = Poet | language = English | nationality = American | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = *University of Washington in Seattle * MFA from the Iowa Writers' Workshop in 1974 | alma_mater = | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = <!-- or: | notablework = --> | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = *1989 Guggenheim Fellowship *NEA fellowship *Washington State Arts Commission grant | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }}
'''Laura Linnea Jensen''' (born November 16, 1948 in [[Tacoma, Washington]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[poet]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=Dt8nO2bOnysC&pg=PA275&dq=Laura+Linnea+Jensen#v=onepage&q=Laura%20Linnea%20Jensen&f=false |chapter=Jensen, Laura Linnea |title=International Who's Who of Authors |publisher=Books.google.com |year=2004 |accessdate=August 23, 2010|isbn=9781857431797 }}</ref>
She graduated from the [[University of Washington in Seattle]], where she studied with [[David Wagoner]], [[Mark Strand]], and [[Galway Kinnell]], and from the [[Iowa Writers' Workshop]] with an MFA in 1974, where she studied with [[Norman Dubie]], [[Donald Justice]], and [[Marvin Bell]]. She became friends with [[Tess Gallagher]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.washington.edu/uwired/outreach/cspn/Website/Classroom%20Materials/Reading%20the%20Region/Northwest%20Schools%20of%20Literature/Commentary/11.html |title=Center for the Study of the Pacific Northwest |publisher=Washington.edu |date= |accessdate=August 23, 2010}}</ref>
Her work appeared in ''Ploughshares''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pshares.org/read/author-detail.cfm?intAuthorID=768 |title=Laura Jensen |publisher=Pshares.org |date= |accessdate=August 23, 2010}}</ref> She read at Burning Word 2005.<ref>{{cite web|author=David Rizzi, xaM Systems |url=http://www.washingtonpoets.org/archive/2005/2005_burning_word_general.php |title=Washington Poets Association-Burning Word 2005 |publisher=Washingtonpoets.org |date= |accessdate=August 23, 2010}}</ref> She lives near [[Wright Park Arboretum|Wright Park]], [[Tacoma, Washington]].<ref>[http://www.poetryfoundation.org/journal/article.html?id=237704 "Lives of the Poets: Laura Jensen"], ''Poetry Foundation'', Heidi Broadhead 9.23.09</ref>
